# OpenWorld — Code Documentation

> **Stack:** React 19 · TypeScript · Vite 8 · Tailwind CSS v4 · Headless UI · Heroicons · Swiper · Vanilla CSS

---

## 1. Project Structure

```
openworld/
├── public/
│   └── icons.svg               # SVG sprite (nav icons)
├── src/
│   ├── assets/
│   │   ├── hero.png
│   │   ├── react.svg
│   │   └── vite.svg
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── Navbar.tsx           # Top navigation bar
│   │   ├── Swiper.tsx           # Image carousel / slider
│   │   └── PostFeed.tsx         # Infinite-scroll post feed
│   ├── App.tsx                  # Root component — page layout
│   ├── App.css                  # Component-level styles
│   ├── index.css                # Global design tokens & resets
│   └── main.tsx                 # React DOM entry point
├── vite.config.ts               # Vite + Tailwind plugin config
└── package.json
```

---

## 2. Entry Point — `main.tsx`

```tsx
import { StrictMode } from 'react'
import { createRoot } from 'react-dom/client'
import './index.css'        // ← Global styles loaded here (once)
import App from './App.tsx'

createRoot(document.getElementById('root')!).render(
  <StrictMode>
    <App />
  </StrictMode>,
)
```

**Flow:**
1. React mounts onto the `#root` div in `index.html`.
2. `index.css` is imported here so global tokens and Tailwind apply everywhere.
3. `<App />` is the single root component that renders the entire page.

---

## 3. Global Styles — `index.css`

```css
@import "tailwindcss";   /* Tailwind v4 — single directive, no config file needed */

:root {
  --text: ...;
  --accent: ...;
  --bg: ...;
  /* ... CSS custom properties (design tokens) ... */
}

@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root { /* dark mode overrides */ }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `@import "tailwindcss"` activates Tailwind v4 via the `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin.
- CSS variables (e.g. `--accent`, `--bg`, `--border`) are the design token system — all components reference these for consistent theming.
- Dark mode is handled automatically via `prefers-color-scheme` media query.

---

## 4. Vite Config — `vite.config.ts`

```ts
import { defineConfig } from "vite";
import react from "@vitejs/plugin-react";
import tailwindcss from "@tailwindcss/vite";

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react(), tailwindcss()],
});
```

- `@vitejs/plugin-react` — enables JSX transform and Fast Refresh (HMR).
- `@tailwindcss/vite` — replaces the old PostCSS setup; processes Tailwind directly in the Vite pipeline.

---

## 5. Root Component — `App.tsx`

```
App
 ├── <Navbar />
 ├── <section id="center">
 │     └── <SliderSwiper />
 ├── <div className="ticks" />      ← decorative tick marks
 ├── <PostFeed />
 ├── <div className="ticks" />
 ├── <section id="next-steps">
 │     ├── #docs  (Portfolio link)
 │     └── #social (GitHub / Discord / X / Bluesky links)
 ├── <div className="ticks" />
 └── <section id="spacer" />
```

**Page layout order (top → bottom):**

| Section | Component / Element | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Navigation | `<Navbar />` | Top bar with links & profile |
| Hero Slider | `<SliderSwiper />` inside `#center` | Image carousel |
| Post Feed | `<PostFeed />` | Infinite-scroll Instagram-like posts |
| Footer Info | `#next-steps` | Portfolio & social links |
| Spacer | `#spacer` | Bottom breathing room |

> **Note:** `useState`, `reactLogo`, and `heroImg` are still imported but not currently used — safe to remove when cleaning up.

