## 6. Component: `Navbar.tsx`

### Libraries Used
| Import | Source | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Disclosure`, `DisclosureButton`, `DisclosurePanel` | `@headlessui/react` | Accessible collapsible mobile menu |
| `Menu`, `MenuButton`, `MenuItem`, `MenuItems` | `@headlessui/react` | Accessible dropdown for profile |
| `Bars3Icon`, `XMarkIcon`, `BellIcon` | `@heroicons/react/24/outline` | SVG icons |

### Data

```ts
const navigation = [
  { name: 'Dashboard', href: '#', current: true },
  { name: 'Team',      href: '#', current: false },
  // ...
]
```
A plain array of route objects. `current: true` marks the active page.

### Helper Function

```ts
function classNames(...classes) {
  return classes.filter(Boolean).join(' ')
}
```
Merges multiple class strings, filtering out falsy values (`undefined`, `false`, `''`). Used to apply conditional Tailwind classes.

### Component Structure

```
Navbar()
 └── <Disclosure as="nav">          ← manages open/closed state internally
       ├── Desktop Nav
       │     ├── Logo (img)
       │     └── navigation.map() → <a> links  (uses classNames() for active style)
       ├── Right Side
       │     ├── Bell icon button (notifications — not wired up)
       │     └── <Menu>             ← profile dropdown
       │           ├── <MenuButton> → avatar image
       │           └── <MenuItems>  → Your profile / Settings / Sign out
       └── <DisclosurePanel>        ← mobile menu (visible on sm: breakpoint)
             └── navigation.map() → <DisclosureButton as="a">
```

**How `Disclosure` works:**
Headless UI manages the open/closed boolean state internally. `DisclosureButton` toggles it. `DisclosurePanel` renders only when open. The hamburger/close icon swap uses `group-data-open:hidden` / `group-data-open:block` Tailwind data attributes.

---

## 7. Component: `Swiper.tsx` (`SliderSwiper`)

### Libraries Used
| Import | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Swiper`, `SwiperSlide` from `swiper/react` | React wrapper for the Swiper carousel |
| `Navigation`, `Pagination`, `A11y` from `swiper/modules` | Swiper feature modules |
| `swiper/css`, `swiper/css/navigation`, `swiper/css/pagination` | Swiper's own stylesheet |

### Data

```ts
const slides = [
  { img: "https://...", label: "Hero 2" },
  // ... 5 items total (Unsplash URLs)
]
```
Static array of slide objects. Each has an image URL and a label.

### Component Structure

```
SliderSwiper()
 └── <div>                          ← Outer wrapper with explicit width/height (400px)
       └── <Swiper                  ← carousel root
             modules={[Navigation, A11y]}
             slidesPerView={1}
             loop={true}            ← wraps around to first slide after last
             navigation             ← shows prev/next arrows
             pagination             ← shows dot indicators
           >
             slides.map() → <SwiperSlide>
               └── <div>            ← flex centering wrapper
                     └── <img>      ← the slide image (objectFit: cover)
```

**Why explicit `width`/`height` on the wrapper?**
Tailwind's preflight CSS resets all elements, which collapses Swiper's internal layout. Setting `width: "100%"` and `height: "400px"` explicitly on the outer div and `style={{ width: "100%", height: "100%" }}` on `<Swiper>` gives Swiper the fixed dimensions it needs to render correctly.

---

## 8. Component: `PostFeed.tsx`

This is the most complex component. It implements infinite scroll with React hooks.

### TypeScript Interface

```ts
interface Post {
  id: number
  username: string
  avatar: string
  image: string
  caption: string
  likes: number
  comments: number
  time: string
  liked: boolean   // tracks like state per post
}
```
Defines the shape of every post object in the feed.

### Module-level Constants

```ts
const UNSPLASH_IMAGES = [...]  // 8 image URLs (cycled via modulo)
const AVATARS = [...]          // 6 avatar URLs (pravatar.cc)
const USERNAMES = [...]        // 6 display names
const CAPTIONS = [...]         // 8 caption strings
let postIdCounter = 0          // global counter — increments per post generated
```

These are defined **outside** the component so they persist across renders and `postIdCounter` never resets to 0 on re-render.

### Helper Function: `generatePosts(count)`

```ts
function generatePosts(count: number): Post[] {
  return Array.from({ length: count }, () => {
    postIdCounter++
    const id = postIdCounter
    return {
      id,
      username: USERNAMES[id % USERNAMES.length],   // cycles through names
      avatar:   AVATARS[id % AVATARS.length],
      image:    UNSPLASH_IMAGES[id % UNSPLASH_IMAGES.length],
      caption:  CAPTIONS[id % CAPTIONS.length],
      likes:    Math.floor(Math.random() * 9000) + 100,
      comments: Math.floor(Math.random() * 300) + 5,
      time:     `${Math.floor(Math.random() * 23) + 1}h ago`,
      liked:    false,
    }
  })
}
```

Creates `count` mock `Post` objects. Uses `id % array.length` (modulo) to cycle through the constant arrays so posts always get valid data.

### Hooks Inside `PostFeed()`

#### `useState` — posts list

```ts
const [posts, setPosts] = useState<Post[]>(() => generatePosts(6))
```
- Initializes with 6 posts.
- The callback form `() => generatePosts(6)` means it only runs once on mount (lazy initializer), not on every render.

#### `useState` — loading flag

```ts
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)
```
`true` while the fake async fetch is running. Controls whether the spinner is shown.

#### `useRef` — sentinel element

```ts
const sentinelRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null)
```
Points to an invisible `<div>` at the very bottom of the feed. The `IntersectionObserver` watches this element.

#### `useCallback` — `loadMore`

```ts
const loadMore = useCallback(() => {
  setLoading(true)
  setTimeout(() => {
    setPosts(prev => [...prev, ...generatePosts(4)])
    setLoading(false)
  }, 800)
}, [])
```
- `useCallback` with `[]` deps means the function reference is stable — it won't be recreated on each render.
- Sets `loading = true`, waits 800ms (simulates a network call), then appends 4 new posts and sets `loading = false`.
- Uses the functional update form `setPosts(prev => ...)` to safely append to existing state.

#### `useEffect` — IntersectionObserver

```ts
useEffect(() => {
  const sentinel = sentinelRef.current
  if (!sentinel) return

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      if (entries[0].isIntersecting && !loading) loadMore()
    },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  )

  observer.observe(sentinel)
  return () => observer.disconnect()   // cleanup on unmount
}, [loading, loadMore])
```
- Creates a native browser `IntersectionObserver` that fires whenever the sentinel div enters the viewport (10% visibility threshold).
- When triggered: if not already loading, calls `loadMore()`.
- The cleanup function `observer.disconnect()` prevents memory leaks when the component unmounts.
- Re-runs when `loading` or `loadMore` changes so the observer always has the latest `loading` value.

#### `toggleLike` — event handler

```ts
const toggleLike = (id: number) => {
  setPosts(prev =>
    prev.map(p =>
      p.id === id
        ? { ...p, liked: !p.liked, likes: p.liked ? p.likes - 1 : p.likes + 1 }
        : p
    )
  )
}
```
Finds the post by `id`, toggles its `liked` boolean, and adjusts the `likes` count accordingly. All other posts are returned unchanged (`p`).

### JSX Structure

```
PostFeed()
 └── <section id="post-feed">
       ├── <h2>Explore</h2>
       └── <div className="posts-grid">        ← CSS Grid (auto-fill, min 320px)
             posts.map() → <article className="post-card">
               ├── .post-header
               │     ├── <img> avatar
               │     ├── .post-meta (username + time)
               │     └── ⋯ more button
               ├── .post-image-wrap → <img loading="lazy">
               ├── .post-actions
               │     ├── ❤️/🤍 like button  (calls toggleLike)
               │     ├── 💬 comment button
               │     ├── 📤 share button
               │     └── 🔖 bookmark button
               ├── .post-likes   (formatted with toLocaleString)
               ├── .post-caption
               └── .post-comments
       └── <div ref={sentinelRef}>             ← invisible trigger for IntersectionObserver
             {loading && <div className="spinner" />}
```

---

## 9. Styling Architecture

| File | Scope | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| `index.css` | Global | CSS custom properties (design tokens), Tailwind import, body/root/heading base styles |
| `App.css` | App-level | Section layouts (`#center`, `#next-steps`, `.ticks`, `#post-feed`), component styles |
| Inline `style={{}}` | Component-local | Used in `Swiper.tsx` to override Tailwind preflight for Swiper's internal layout |
| Tailwind classes | `Navbar.tsx` | Utility classes via `className=""` (dark overlay, spacing, responsive breakpoints) |

**Design token flow:**
```
index.css :root { --accent: #aa3bff }
    ↓
App.css .post-avatar { border: 2px solid var(--accent-border) }
    ↓
Automatically switches in dark mode via @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)
```

---

## 10. Data Flow Diagram

```
main.tsx
  └─ renders <App>
        ├─ <Navbar>
        │    └─ navigation[] array → mapped to <a> links
        │    └─ Headless UI manages disclosure/menu state internally
        │
        ├─ <SliderSwiper>
        │    └─ slides[] array → mapped to <SwiperSlide>
        │    └─ Swiper library manages current slide index internally
        │
        └─ <PostFeed>
             ├─ State: posts[]  ──────────────────────────────┐
             ├─ State: loading                                │
             ├─ Ref:   sentinelRef → IntersectionObserver     │
             │              └─ on intersect → loadMore()      │
             │                    └─ setTimeout 800ms         │
             │                          └─ generatePosts(4) ──┘
             │                               └─ appends to posts[]
             └─ toggleLike(id) → immutable posts[] update
```

---

